values.description:
This pull request captures our latest work in getting haptix_comm to work on Windows, namely:

* Enable building of the stuff in `example/` (by copying a bunch of CMake code, as we've done elsewhere).
* Add the abilitiy to choose between Debug and Release when configuring.
* Add a Visual Studio property sheet that can be used later to configure for building against this thing.
* Add a script (`make_sdk.bat`) that automates bundling an entire binary SDK.  With some tweaks, it should be possible to make a Jenkins job that runs that script.
values.title: More Windows changes

values.description:
This pull request implements the generation of MATLAB mex files on Windows.

The whole thing is quite a hack, since we are using cmake variables to compose a Windows command to be run directly in the command line, which turns into problems when cmake variable are more than just a string.

There are some other approaches out there, trying not to use the mex command (is not really more than some special configurations/flags for the compiler) but call the compiler directly using compiler + mex flags. I prefer to use the direct call to the mex script.

[This is the testing run on jenkins](http://build.osrfoundation.org/job/haptix_comm-any-devel-windows7-amd64/51/) which generates the [.mex files](http://build.osrfoundation.org/job/haptix_comm-any-devel-windows7-amd64/ws/workspace/haptix-comm/build/matlab/).
values.title: Auto MEX files generation using MATLAB

values.description:
These are modifications of `hx_controller.c` with the following changes:

* `joints_stress` (note the plural joints): multiples sinusoidal amplitude and frequency by `argc`, so that invoking the example with multiple (arbitrary) command-line arguments will increase the severity of the reference trajectory.

* `joint_stress`: runs sinusoidal trajectory modified by `argc` for one joint at a time in sequence.

~~~
cd haptix-comm/examples
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make
~~~
~~~
./joints_stress
./joints_stress ow
./joints_stress ow hurting
./joints_stress ow hurting stop
~~~
~~~
./joint_stress one
./joint_stress one at
./joint_stress one at a
./joint_stress one at a time
~~~
values.title: Add controller examples for physics stress testing
